    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pieces of wood or another material, used to receive the blow of a hammer or other device for the purpose of producing sound. An example is the disk-shaped striking block used with a gavel (ceremonial mallet) in courts, as when a judge bangs a gavel to start a session.</Note_Text>
